# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Blacklight app  —  .gitignore
#  NEVER commit: dependency caches, build output, or real registry data.
#  Lives at the app root:  C:\Users\Admin\Desktop\blacklight-app\.gitignore
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ---- Node / npm (the Tauri frontend dependencies) ----
# node_modules is huge and reinstallable with `npm install`.
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*
# NOTE: package-lock.json IS committed (locks exact dep versions) — not ignored.

# ---- Rust / Tauri build output (huge, regenerated every build) ----
# This also covers the finished installer under target/release/bundle/.
shell/src-tauri/target/
target/
# NOTE: Cargo.lock IS committed for an app (reproducible builds) — not ignored.

# ---- Python engine: PyInstaller freeze output (regenerated each freeze) ----
# build/ and dist/ are recreated every time; the *.spec recipe is KEPT (not ignored).
engine/build/
engine/dist/
build/
dist/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ---- ⛔ CRITICAL: real registry exports live here — NEVER upload ----
# engine\backups\ holds .reg files exported from YOUR machine (e.g. that 68-entry
# BAM export). *.reg anywhere is blocked as a belt-and-suspenders privacy guard.
engine/backups/
*.reg

# ---- Tauri sidecar binary (the frozen Python engine .exe) ----
# IGNORED: this .exe is a rebuildable PyInstaller artifact. Regenerate it any
# time from engine\ (pyinstaller --onefile ...), then copy into binaries\.
# Keeps the repo lean and avoids committing a 6 MB binary.
shell/src-tauri/binaries/

# ---- OS / editor cruft ----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/

# ---- Secrets / local env ----
.env
.env.*
*.local